<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880721-0043 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Hercules Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HPC </CO><IN> ERN </IN><TEXT>   Hercules Inc. reported that second-quarter net income declined 29% to $47.3 million, or $1 a share, from $67 million, or $1.19 a share, a year earlier.    The Wilmington, Del.-based chemical and aerospace concern cited higher raw-material costs for its fibers and film businesses and heavy development investments in its aerospace unit. The year-ago results included gains from the sale of assets of $6.4 million, or 11 cents a share.    Sales rose about 2% to $704.7 million from $691.5 million.    Hercules said specialty chemical profits rose only slightly to $37 million from $36 million. Engineered polymers declined 69% to $4 million from $13 million. And aerospace earnings declined 25% to $15 million from $20 million.    For the six months, net income declined 56% to $87.1 million, or $1.81 a share, from $199.1 million, or $3.51 a share. The year-ago results included gains from the sale of assets of $90.5 million, or $1.58 a share. Six-month sales remained about flat. </TEXT></DOC>